Syncrude Reduces Staff at Aurora Site in Alberta on Forest Fires

-- B y   C o l i n   M c C l e l l a n d
-- 
2011-05-30T12:39:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/syncrude-reduces-staff-at-aurora-site-in-alberta-on-forest-fires.html
“Significant” smoke from forest
fires approaching Syncrude Ltd.’s Aurora operations in northern
 Alberta  requires the plant to maintain reduced staffing levels
until further notice, the company said in a  statement .  The operation is currently not at risk, Syncrude said.
Production and staffing levels at Mildred Lake remain normal,
the company said. Staffing levels at Aurora were last “normal”
on May 24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colin McClelland in Toronto at 
 cmcclelland1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at   dstets@bloomberg.net . 